            <div n="r" type="textpart">
               <p>
                  <milestone n="1" unit="line"/> … in Diospolis, so that s/he bear witness to your love in God. Greet in the Lord our most longed-for daughter Marciana together with all those in our house, 
beloved and cared-for by God, to which (house?) the Lord will repay as befits their labors. 
<milestone n="9" unit="line"/> I am amazed that, although I have written to you many times, you did not deem it worthy to write me a letter of greeting.
Let me have this benefit from you in the Lord and be healthy for my sake in the Lord!
               </p>
            </div>
            <div n="v" type="textpart">
               <p>
                  <milestone n="14" unit="line"/> … to Ploution, priest and confessor, (from) Lucius. 
<note>Translation: L. Berkes and W.G. Claytor, Vigiliae Christianae 79, 205</note>
               </p>
            </div>
         </div>
